furious dictates of his unruly and ungenerous de|fire;
upon which, with an air of cool determi|nation,
&s;he demanded a parley; and when, upon
her repeated reque&s;t, he granted it, addre&s;&s;ed her|&s;elf
to him in the&s;e words, while her eyes gleam|ed
with all the dignity of the mo&s;t awful re&s;ent|ment.
&ldquo;Sir, I &s;corn to upbraid you with a re|petition
