he would take &s;ome &s;tep of this kind to retrieve
<PB N="32" REF="37">
her favour, had gone abroad on pretence of vi|&s;iting,
after having &s;ignified to her kin&s;man, her
re&s;olution to avoid the company of Peregrine, on
account of &s;ome ambiguities which (&s;he &s;aid)
