obtaining Emilia's forgivene&s;s.</P>
<P>Peregrine's pride was kindled by this blunt de|claration,
which he could not help con&s;idering as
the re&s;ult of a &s;cheme concerted betwixt the
young lady and her uncle, in order to take the ad|vantage
