<P>His fears were then all over, but mine recurred
with double aggravation: I dreaded the &s;ight of
my father, and &s;hared all the &s;orrow he &s;uffered on
account of my undutiful behaviour: for I loved
him with &s;uch piety of affection, that I would
have endured every other &s;pecies of di&s;tre&s;s, rather
<PB N="78" REF="83">
than have given him the lea&s;t unea&s;ine&s;s: but
love (where he reigns in full empire) is altoge|ther
