me for one of her own &s;i&s;terhood.</P>
<P>I no &s;ooner perceived her opinion, than I de|&s;ired
lord W&mdash;m to undeceive her; upon
which &s;he was made acquainted with the predica|ment
in which I &s;tood, and &s;hewed us into a pri|vate
