She was undoubtedly a woman of great &s;pirit
and under&s;tanding, but &s;ubject to an infirmity
which very much impairs and di&s;gui&s;es every other
qualification.</P>
<P>In about three weeks after our marriage, I was
&s;o happy as to obtain the forgivene&s;s of my fa|ther,
to who&s;e hou&s;e we repaired, in order to pay
our re&s;pects and &s;ubmi&s;&s;ion. At &s;ight of me he
