that attended the conver&s;ion of St.
Paul?&endq; While they were employed in the ex|erci&s;e
of their devotion, our hero and his atten|dant
retired by the back-door, which opened in|to
the fields; and while Pipes went in pur&s;uit of
his calf, which had taken &s;helter under the wall,
his ma&s;ter proceeded forwards to the place from
whence he had come, where he had agreed to
meet Cadwallader, and communicate the &s;ucce&s;s
<PB N="243" REF="248">
of his enterprize, with which he was perfectly
