pre&s;uming upon his knowledge of her ad|venture,
began to make love with great vehe|mence.
At fir&s;t, &s;he pretended to take offence
at his pre&s;umption; but, perceiving from certain
<PB N="245" REF="250">
in&s;inuations which he artfully dropp'd, that he
